Deverus 2025-08-10 03:44 p.m.
Yes, your honour, EST.

In brief; Paragraph 9 is wholly untrue. The Lieutenant Governor/PPT have since attempted three times to submit a writ of election to the Mayflower Electoral Commission. I'll attach those below. Even so- it is not the Lieutenant Governor who is responsible constitutionally for declaring the County Executive or County Government defunct, it is simply constitutionally defunct by law. This has been determined, as stated, once by the Mayflower Electoral Commission on November 10th, 2024, and again by the Court in JamesGardai vs. LCPD CV-407-25 (2025) on April 19th of this Year.
https://discord.com/channels/1183291978499235890/1242316503072768131/1308555256380260455
https://discord.com/channels/1183291978499235890/1242316503072768131/1318752356422123540
https://discord.com/channels/1183291978499235890/1242316503072768131/1320886855062917121

Furthermore, the facts where it concerns the Holdover doctrine in People ex rel. Lamm v. Banta are entirely different. The Colorado Constitution does have a codified holdover provision, specifically: Article XII 1 of the Colorado Constitution. The holdover doctrine, as a general rule, requires that there is a statutory or constitutional silence on what happens after a term ends, or in the event there is a vacancy- in Tilton, which is among the oldest and most widely cited cases on the matter, was grounded in California's own constitution and statutes. Here this simply isn't the case, the Mayflower Constitution explicitly has a self-removal mechanism for prolonged absence, and deliberately grants the authority of those offices to its respective state offices- that being the Senate and Governor.

Holdover doctrine is designed specifically to avoid lapses in governance- in this instance, where the power of those offices is transferred higher- there is no such lapse. Governance continues, just at a higher level.

Also, last side note on this, but the holdover doctrine argument is defeated by Respondent's own actions, whereby Senator DanielCrusoe became President of the Board and then County Executive. It's important to note that Senator DanielCrusoe never held such an office- Arvantise was the only person to legitimately do so. There's just an inconsistency in their arguments vs their actions which doesn't make sense.
